# Design System Rules

This project uses a design token system. **Always use tokens instead of hardcoded values.**

## Colors

Use colors from `src/tokens.json`. Never use hardcoded hex colors.

### Brand Colors
- Primary: `brand-500` (#43389B)
- Hover: `brand-600` (#362D7C)
- Active: `brand-700` (#28225D)

### Gray Cool (UI Colors)
- `gray-cool-25` to `gray-cool-950`
- Text primary: `gray-cool-900` (#111322)
- Text secondary: `gray-cool-700` (#404968)
- Text tertiary: `gray-cool-600` (#4A5578)
- Border: `gray-cool-100` (#E9EBF1), `gray-cool-200` (#DCDFEA)
- Background hover: `gray-cool-50` (#F6F6F9)

### Semantic Colors
- Error: `error-500` (#F04438), `error-600` (#D92D20)
- Warning: `warning-500` (#F79009), `warning-600` (#DC6803)
- Success: `success-500` (#17B26A), `success-600` (#079455)

### Background Colors
Use tokens from `colors.background`:
- `bg-primary` (#FFFFFF)
- `bg-primary-hover` (#F6F6F9)
- `bg-secondary` (#F6F6F9)
- `bg-disabled` (#E9EBF1)

### Text Colors
Use tokens from `colors.text`:
- `text-primary-900` (#111322)
- `text-secondary-700` (#404968)
- `text-disabled` (#5D6B98)
- `text-placeholder` (#7D89B0)

## Spacing

Always use spacing tokens from `src/tokens.json`:

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `none` | 0px | No spacing |
| `xxs` | 2px | Minimal spacing |
| `xs` | 4px | Small gaps, small padding |
| `sm` | 6px | Small spacing |
| `md` | 8px | Medium spacing |
| `lg` | 12px | Large spacing |
| `xl` | 16px | Extra large spacing |
| `2xl` | 20px | Section spacing |
| `3xl` | 24px | Large section spacing |
| `4xl` | 32px | Major spacing |

### Button Specific Spacing
- Gap sm/md buttons: `xs` (4px)
- Gap lg buttons: `sm` (6px)
- Horizontal padding sm/md: `lg-14px` (14px)
- Horizontal padding lg: `xl` (16px)

## Border Radius

Always use radius tokens:

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `none` | 0px | No radius |
| `xxs` | 2px | Minimal radius |
| `xs` | 4px | Small elements, badges, shortcuts |
| `sm` | 6px | Small components |
| `md` | 8px | Buttons, cards, inputs |
| `lg` | 10px | Larger cards |
| `xl` | 12px | Modals |
| `2xl` | 16px | Large containers |
| `full` | 9999px | Pills, avatars |

## Shadows

Use the skeuomorphic shadow pattern from Figma:

```css
/* Primary/Destructive buttons */
shadow-[0_1px_2px_0_rgba(10,13,18,0.05)]
after:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_rgba(125,137,176,0.2),inset_0_-2px_0_0_rgba(64,73,104,0.1)]

/* Secondary buttons */
shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_rgba(125,137,176,0.2),inset_0_-2px_0_0_rgba(64,73,104,0.1),0_1px_2px_0_rgba(10,13,18,0.05)]

/* Disabled state */
shadow-[0_1px_2px_0_rgba(10,13,18,0.05)]
```

## Typography

Always use typography tokens from `src/tokens.json`. Never use arbitrary font values.

### Font Family
| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `font-family-display` | Inter | Headings, display text |
| `font-family-body` | Inter | Body text, UI elements |

### Font Weight
| Token | Value | CSS Weight | Usage |
|-------|-------|------------|-------|
| `regular` | Regular | 400 | Body text, labels |
| `medium` | Medium | 500 | Buttons, emphasis |
| `semibold` | Semibold | 600 | Strong emphasis |
| `bold` | Bold | 700 | Headings, important |

### Font Size (Text)
| Token | Size | Line Height | Usage |
|-------|------|-------------|-------|
| `text-2xs` | 10px | 14px | Tiny labels, avatar initials (xs) |
| `text-xxs` | 11px | 16px | Very small labels, avatar initials (sm), kbd hints |
| `text-xs` | 12px | 18px | Small labels, captions, shortcuts |
| `text-sm` | 14px | 20px | Body text, buttons (sm/md) |
| `text-md` | 16px | 24px | Large buttons, body |
| `text-lg` | 18px | 28px | Subheadings |
| `text-xl` | 20px | 30px | Section titles |

### Font Size (Display)
| Token | Size | Line Height | Usage |
|-------|------|-------------|-------|
| `display-xs` | 24px | 32px | Small headings |
| `display-sm` | 30px | 38px | Section headings |
| `display-md` | 36px | 44px | Page headings |
| `display-lg` | 48px | 60px | Hero headings |
| `display-xl` | 60px | 72px | Large hero text |
| `display-2xl` | 72px | 90px | Extra large display |

### Typography in Tailwind
```css
/* Use typography token classes (include line-height automatically) */
text-2xs     /* 10px/14px */
text-xxs     /* 11px/16px */
text-xs      /* 12px/18px */
text-sm      /* 14px/20px */
text-md      /* 16px/24px */
text-lg      /* 18px/28px */
text-xl      /* 20px/30px */
text-display-xs   /* 24px/32px */
text-display-sm   /* 30px/38px */
text-display-md   /* 36px/44px */
text-display-lg   /* 48px/60px */
text-display-xl   /* 60px/72px */
text-display-2xl  /* 72px/90px */

/* Font families */
font-display  /* Inter - for headings */
font-body     /* Inter - for body text */

/* Font weights */
font-normal   /* 400 - regular */
font-medium   /* 500 - medium */
font-semibold /* 600 - semibold */
font-bold     /* 700 - bold */
```

### Important: Line Heights Are Included
When using `text-xs`, `text-sm`, etc., the line-height is **automatically included** from the Tailwind config. Do NOT add explicit `leading-[Xpx]` classes unless overriding.

## Icons

**Always use Untitled UI Icons** for all icons in the project.

### Package
- Package: `@untitledui/icons`
- Documentation: https://github.com/untitleduico/icons
- Style: Stroke-based (outline) icons

### Usage
```tsx
import { ArrowRight, Plus, Check, XClose } from '@untitledui/icons';

// In components
<ArrowRight size={20} />
<Plus size={16} />

// With Button component
<Button iconStart={<ArrowRight size={20} />}>Continue</Button>
<Button iconEnd={<Check size={20} />}>Confirm</Button>
```

### Icon Sizes
| Context | Size | Usage |
|---------|------|-------|
| Small buttons | 16px | `size={16}` |
| Medium buttons | 20px | `size={20}` |
| Large buttons | 20px | `size={20}` |
| Standalone icons | 24px | `size={24}` |

### Common Icons
- Navigation: `ArrowRight`, `ArrowLeft`, `ArrowUp`, `ArrowDown`, `ChevronRight`, `ChevronDown`
- Actions: `Plus`, `Minus`, `Check`, `XClose`, `Edit`, `Trash`
- UI: `Search`, `Menu`, `Settings`, `User`, `Home`
- Files: `File`, `Folder`, `Download`, `Upload`, `Copy`
- Communication: `Mail`, `Bell`, `MessageSquare`

### DO NOT
❌ Use other icon libraries (Heroicons, Lucide, FontAwesome, etc.)
❌ Create custom SVG icons without checking Untitled UI first
❌ Use different icon sizes within the same context

### DO
✅ Always import from `@untitledui/icons`
✅ Use consistent sizes based on context
✅ Pass icons as React nodes to component props

## Component Patterns

### Buttons
- Always use the `Button` component from `src/components/ui/button.tsx`
- Use variant props: `primary`, `secondary-gray`, `tertiary-gray`, `link-gray`, `link-color`, `destructive`
- Use size props: `sm` (36px), `md` (40px), `lg` (44px), `icon`
- Support icons via `iconStart` and `iconEnd` props (use Untitled UI Icons)
- Support keyboard shortcuts via `shortcut` prop

### Shortcuts
- Use the `Shortcut` component from `src/components/ui/shortcut.tsx`
- Use `theme="dark"` for primary/destructive buttons
- Use `theme="light"` for secondary/tertiary buttons

## DO NOT

❌ Use hardcoded hex colors like `#43389B` - use token references
❌ Use arbitrary pixel values for spacing - use spacing tokens
❌ Use arbitrary border-radius values - use radius tokens
❌ Use arbitrary font sizes like `text-[10px]` or `text-[14px]` - use typography tokens (`text-2xs`, `text-sm`, etc.)
❌ Use explicit `leading-[Xpx]` with token font sizes - line-height is already included
❌ Create new color values without adding to tokens
❌ Use `opacity` for disabled states - use proper disabled color tokens
❌ Use icon libraries other than Untitled UI Icons
❌ Create custom SVG icons without checking Untitled UI first

## DO

✅ Reference tokens from `src/tokens.json`
✅ Use semantic color names (e.g., `text-primary`, `bg-disabled`)
✅ Use consistent spacing scale
✅ Use typography tokens for all text
✅ Follow the component API patterns
✅ Use Tailwind classes with token values
✅ Keep disabled states using proper tokens, not opacity
✅ Use Untitled UI Icons (`@untitledui/icons`) for all icons

## File Structure

```
src/
├── components/
│   └── ui/
│       ├── button.tsx      # Button component
│       ├── shortcut.tsx    # Shortcut badge component
│       └── *.stories.tsx   # Storybook stories
├── lib/
│   └── utils.ts            # cn() utility
└── tokens.json             # Design tokens
```

## Adding New Components

1. Create component in `src/components/ui/`
2. Use `cva` for variant-based styling
3. Use `cn()` for class merging
4. Reference tokens for all colors, spacing, radius
5. Create corresponding `.stories.tsx` file
6. Export from component file

